---
import LegalLayout from "~/layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import { getLocalizedPath } from "~/i18n/utils";

const terms = getLocalizedPath("/terms", "en");
const subprocessors = getLocalizedPath("/subprocessors", "en");

const title = "AwesomeBot Privacy Policy";
const description =
  "How AwesomeBot processes personal data: controller and processor roles, data categories, subprocessors, data residency, retention and your rights.";
---

<LegalLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  eyebrow="Data protection"
  heading="Privacy Policy"
  lastUpdated="Effective 10 July 2026"
  slugs={{ pl: "/prywatnosc", en: "/privacy" }}
>
  <p class="legal-lead">
    This policy explains how we process personal data in connection with the AwesomeBot product and
    the website presenting it (the "Landing"). We state exactly what we collect, why, whom we entrust
    it to, and where it is physically stored.
  </p>

  <div class="legal-card">
    <p>
      <strong>Controller:</strong> Awesome Works AI Rafał Łazicki (sole proprietorship), ul. Wojska
      Polskiego 43, Warsaw, Poland, VAT ID PL5223202536 (the "<strong>AwesomeWorks</strong>", "<strong>we</strong>").
    </p>
    <p><strong>Contact for data protection matters:</strong> hello@awesomeworks.ai</p>
  </div>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">1.</span>Two roles: controller and processor</h2>
  <p>
    AwesomeBot is a multi-tenant service used by medical clinics and property-management firms,
    housing communities and cooperatives (the "Clients"). Depending on the type of data, we act in
    one of two roles:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Controller</strong> — for the data of Landing visitors, people requesting a Demo call,
      Client User accounts, and correspondence with us.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Processor</strong> — for the data of persons contacting the Client (patients,
      residents, vendors) processed in AwesomeBot on the Client's behalf. Here the
      <strong>Client is the controller</strong>, and our basis is a data processing agreement (DPA).
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    If you are a patient, resident or vendor and wish to exercise your rights regarding data handled
    in AwesomeBot, direct your request to the relevant Client (the controller); you may also write to
    us at hello@awesomeworks.ai and we will forward it.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">2.</span>Data we process as controller</h2>
  <h3>a) Landing visitors</h3>
  <p>
    Technical data needed to display the site and keep it secure (including IP address, browser type,
    server log data).
  </p>
  <h3>b) Demo call</h3>
  <p>
    When you request a demonstration conversation with an AI agent, we process the
    <strong>phone number you provide</strong> and your device's <strong>IP address</strong> — to
    place the call and enforce abuse-prevention limits.
  </p>
  <h3>c) Client User accounts</h3>
  <p>
    Email address and a secured (argon2id-hashed) password, workspace memberships and roles, and
    technical login records (email and IP of a login attempt) for security purposes.
  </p>
  <h3>d) Correspondence</h3>
  <p>Data you provide when contacting us (e.g. by email at hello@awesomeworks.ai).</p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">3.</span>Data processed on the Client's behalf</h2>
  <p>
    While handling messages and calls for the Client, the following may be processed, depending on
    the content of the contact:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>phone numbers</strong> and <strong>email addresses</strong> of contacting persons;</li>
    <li><strong>message content</strong> (phone, SMS, email) and <strong>voicemail content</strong>;</li>
    <li><strong>transcripts</strong> of voice conversations (browser and phone) and voicemail;</li>
    <li><strong>call recordings</strong> from the AI voice agent (stored at the voice-platform provider — see section 6);</li>
    <li>
      <strong>case data</strong> entered or generated during handling (e.g. unit number, report
      history, reply drafts, priority reasons).
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The scope and purposes of this processing are determined by the Client as controller. Where the
    Client is a medical clinic, processing may involve <strong>health data</strong> (a special
    category, Art. 9 GDPR) — the Client is responsible for the appropriate legal basis. We do not use
    this data for our own purposes.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">4.</span>Purposes and legal bases (data for which we are controller)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Displaying and securing the Landing, preventing abuse — Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest).</li>
    <li>Placing a Demo call at your request — Art. 6(1)(a) (consent) and (f).</li>
    <li>Creating and maintaining User accounts, providing the Service to the Client — Art. 6(1)(b) (contract) and (f).</li>
    <li>Handling correspondence and complaints — Art. 6(1)(f), and (c) for complaints.</li>
    <li>Establishing or defending claims, tax and accounting obligations — Art. 6(1)(c) and (f).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">5.</span>Automation and artificial intelligence</h2>
  <p>
    AwesomeBot uses AI models to classify messages, set priorities, transcribe speech and prepare
    reply drafts. These are <strong>assistive</strong> — outbound communication requires human
    approval on the Client's side. We do not make decisions about data subjects based solely on
    automated processing that would produce legal or similarly significant effects on them within the
    meaning of Art. 22 GDPR.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">6.</span>Recipients and subprocessors</h2>
  <p>
    To provide the Service we use trusted providers to whom we entrust processing under data
    processing agreements. Key subprocessors:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>OpenAI</strong> — language models (classification, reply drafting), speech
      transcription (Whisper) and vector embeddings. Transfer outside the EEA is safeguarded by
      Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC) and a DPA.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>ElevenLabs</strong> — speech synthesis and the voice-agent platform; this provider
      <strong>stores call recordings</strong>. It provides <strong>data residency</strong> and a DPA.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Telnyx</strong> — telephony (numbers, routing of calls and messages).
      <strong>Data is processed in Germany (EU)</strong>. DPA in place.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Twilio</strong> — SMS delivery (internal escalation notifications). Transfer outside the
      EEA safeguarded by SCC and a DPA.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Hetzner Online GmbH</strong> — hosting of the application infrastructure and database.
      <strong>The server and database are located in Germany (Nuremberg data centre, EU)</strong>.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    A full list with data categories and processing locations is in the
    <a href={subprocessors}>Subprocessor List</a>. Data may also be disclosed to bodies authorised by
    law and, to the necessary extent, to our advisers.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">7.</span>Transfers outside the EEA</h2>
  <p>
    Some subprocessors (OpenAI, Twilio) process data outside the European Economic Area (including in
    the USA). In such cases the transfer relies on <strong>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC)</strong>
    with additional safeguards. <strong>The hosting infrastructure (server and database) and Telnyx
    telephony remain within the EU (Germany)</strong>. You can obtain information about the safeguards
    used by writing to hello@awesomeworks.ai.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">8.</span>Retention periods</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Voice call records</strong> (metadata and transcripts in the Service) — as a rule <strong>up to 30 days</strong>.</li>
    <li><strong>Demo call data</strong> (phone number, IP) — <strong>up to 30 days</strong>.</li>
    <li><strong>Login attempt records</strong> — about 24 hours.</li>
    <li><strong>Call recordings</strong> — per the retention settings of the voice-platform provider (ElevenLabs).</li>
    <li><strong>Client account, message and case data</strong> — for the term of the agreement; afterwards deleted or returned per the DPA.</li>
    <li><strong>Billing data and documentation</strong> — for the period required by law and until claims are time-barred.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">9.</span>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    You have the right to: access your data, rectification, erasure, restriction of processing, data
    portability, objection to processing based on legitimate interest, and — for data processed based
    on consent — to withdraw it at any time (without affecting the lawfulness of processing before
    withdrawal).
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>For matters where we are the <strong>controller</strong>, direct requests to hello@awesomeworks.ai.</li>
    <li>For contacting persons' data (where we are the processor), the controller is the <strong>Client</strong> — direct your request to them; we will support its fulfilment.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority — in Poland the
    <strong>President of the Personal Data Protection Office (PUODO)</strong>, ul. Stawki 2, 00-193
    Warsaw.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">10.</span>Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    The Landing uses cookies and similar technologies necessary for its operation and security and,
    with your consent, for analytics. You can manage cookie settings in your browser.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">11.</span>Data security</h2>
  <p>
    We apply technical and organisational measures appropriate to the risk, including: hard isolation
    of each Client's data at the database level (Row-Level Security), password hashing (argon2id),
    session tokens, restricting operator-panel access to a private network only, no publicly exposed
    database ports, and keeping access keys to external services server-side.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">12.</span>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy (e.g. when the scope of the Service, the law or the subprocessor list
    changes). The current version and its effective date are published on the Landing; we will inform
    Clients of material changes. Use of the Service is governed by the <a href={terms}>Terms of Service</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
